Help & usage information about Pacific Star  1.0 By Rohan Bhardwaj
This file contains information about usage and operations regarding
this software. Remote Computer Explorer for 32-Bit Windows is a
program that allows you to connect to other computers and
manipulate data on them. You can view the files as if they were on
your own computer, and you can even download them to your
computer for viewing as well as delete files on the RemoteHost.
Before proceeding with any operations, please bear in mind that
deleting or otherwise altering files on a host, *peeking* on data,
and pulling the plug may be illegal (and certainly *is* unethical).
When you have selected in the main window the file you want to
download, click the download button on the toolbar, or use the
HotKey Ctrl+F1 to download and save the file to your hard drive.
When you have selected the file to delete in the main window, click
the delete button or use the HotKey Ctrl+F2.
Click the Tools button on the toolbar or use the Ctrl+F5 shortcut to
Click Messages on the toolbar to send a pop-up message to the host
Send a URL Jump message to force the user of the remote computer
to go to the specified web site.
Please bear in mind that your actions may be a cause of repent if you
are not careful enough. The author is in no way responsible for any
situations arising out of use of this software program.
